    "body": "@iSOcH As the old package is now replaced with a new one, we expect this should no longer be an issue. The old one had its versioning wrong; say, instead of 1.25.1, it had 1.2510. So, you won't see any updates as 1.2510 is considered greater than 1.25.1. Therefore, starting from the next release, PPA users will need to do the following before updating Nethermind:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\napt-get purge nethermind\r\napt-get update\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is basically what you've done above. Feel free to reopen this issue if you encounter any problems on our next release. We'll communicate this change accordingly.",
